# CAP LOOP EQUATIONS FOR HONEY BEE FORAGING

1. CONSTRAINT EQUATIONS
   C1. Distance Encoding:
   waggle_duration = 0.004725 * distance_m
   
   C2. Forager Conservation:
   N_available(t) + N_committed(t) ≤ 49
   
   C3. Dance Floor Limit:
   max_dancers = 5
1. ALIGNMENT EQUATIONS
   A1. Recruitment Strength:
   followers(t) = 4.842 * dancers * quality * exp(-0.408 * d/d_max)
   
   A2. Recruitment Rate:
   μ = followers/dancers ≈ 2.038
   
   A3. Spatial Alignment:
   κ = 1/σ²(angles) = 0.4046
1. PERSISTENCE EQUATIONS
   P1. Resource Extraction:
   dR/dt = η * N_committed * quality - δ * R
   
   P2. Temporal Memory:
   corr(N_committed(t), N_committed(t+1)) > 0.5
   
   P3. Quorum Threshold:
   θ_quorum = 8 followers
1. FEEDBACK (NEW CONSTRAINTS)
   F1. Scout Limitation:
   N_scouts(t+1) = 49 - N_committed(t)
   
   F2. Quality Depletion:
   quality(t+1) = quality(t) * exp(-ε * harvest(t))

COMPLETE SYSTEM:
dN_committed/dt = α * A(t) * N_available(t) - γ * N_committed(t)
dquality/dt = -ε * N_committed(t) * quality(t)
dR/dt = η * N_committed(t) * quality(t) - δ * R(t)

where:
A(t) = recruitment alignment function
N_available(t) = 49 - N_committed(t)
